WEBVTT

00:01.542 --> 00:02.667
(narrator)
Previously on "Hellcats  ...  "

00:02.667 --> 00:05.458
Mom, what is this? It says
my scholarship was canceled.

00:05.458 --> 00:06.708
You're applying
for a scholarship?

00:06.708 --> 00:08.083
I have one now.
For cheerleading.

00:08.083 --> 00:10.000
Hello, Marti.
Welcome to Cheertown.

00:10.000 --> 00:12.333
Vanessa, I'm sure you remember
the famous coach Red Raymond.

00:12.333 --> 00:14.625
So we're clear
I have a boyfriend.

00:14.625 --> 00:17.542
- Things change.
- Hi, I'm Vanessa Lodge.

00:17.542 --> 00:19.834
- My girlfriend.
- Nice to meet you.

00:19.834 --> 00:22.166
- Tighten up!
- Oh!

00:22.166 --> 00:24.667
Six weeks?
I'll miss qualifiers.

00:24.667 --> 00:27.208
Lewis asked Vanessa if he could
make you his permanent flyer.

00:27.208 --> 00:29.291
(Marti)
What about Alice?
Weren't they, like, a thing?

00:29.291 --> 00:30.834
The squad comes first.

00:30.834 --> 00:33.166
Hey, Savannah,
you wanna go out with me?

00:33.166 --> 00:34.542
Okay, yeah.

00:34.542 --> 00:36.667
♪ One two three four five ♪

00:36.667 --> 00:40.041
♪ Look to the left
Look to the right ♪♪

00:40.041 --> 00:42.750
[Vita Chambers
singing "Like Boom"]

00:42.750 --> 00:47.375
♪ Yeah yeah
my friends say I'm crazy ♪

00:47.375 --> 00:50.166
(Vanessa)
'What? Do you realize what
you're doing to these girls?'

00:51.542 --> 00:53.291
You've gotta be kidding me.

00:53.291 --> 00:55.000
They've worked just as hard
as the volleyball team.

00:55.000 --> 00:56.917
♪ Not even worth ignoring ♪

00:56.917 --> 01:01.250
♪ It's just what
I'm addicted to hey ♪

01:05.208 --> 01:07.542
♪ It's like boom ♪♪

01:07.542 --> 01:08.834
Whoa.

01:08.834 --> 01:11.208
I bought this
for my date with Dan.

01:11.208 --> 01:13.542
What does this dress say?

01:13.542 --> 01:16.166
Back off.
This is my street corner.

01:16.166 --> 01:19.834
- What, really?
- No, I'm kidding. You look hot.

01:19.834 --> 01:21.417
Why are you asking me, anyways?

01:21.417 --> 01:24.417
Well, he's your friend
and I want it to go well.

01:24.417 --> 01:26.875
Believe it or not, I don't
get asked out that much.

01:26.875 --> 01:29.041
Well, you'd never know it
from your streetwise cool.

01:29.041 --> 01:31.792
[chuckles]
Marti, come on.

01:31.792 --> 01:33.959
This is my first secular date.

01:33.959 --> 01:36.708
I'm used to group dates
stage-managed by my church.

01:36.708 --> 01:37.792
I'm sorry. It's just...

01:37.792 --> 01:39.750
[sighs]
It's weird.

01:39.750 --> 01:42.417
'I mean, you dating Dan
of all people.'

01:42.417 --> 01:44.708
All people?

01:44.708 --> 01:46.250
All people.
What does that even mean?

01:46.250 --> 01:48.291
Well, for one thing,
he's big and you're little.

01:48.291 --> 01:50.750
I mean, you two could be
Russian nesting dolls.

01:50.750 --> 01:52.917
But, um, mostly, he's...

01:53.875 --> 01:56.208
...he's a player.

01:56.208 --> 01:57.834
You're not the kind
of girl he dates.

01:57.834 --> 01:58.917
What kind of girl
does he date?

01:58.917 --> 02:00.875
Party girls, hookups.

02:00.875 --> 02:03.000
You're relationship material.
He's not used to that.

02:04.417 --> 02:06.792
Marti, why are you
being so negative?

02:08.917 --> 02:10.959
- Do you have a thing for Dan?
- What?

02:10.959 --> 02:13.000
- If you do, I'll back off.
- No.

02:13.000 --> 02:14.458
I don't wanna create drama
within the squad.

02:14.458 --> 02:16.291
Dan and I are just buds.

02:16.291 --> 02:18.917
I mean, we're friends.
You know? That's it, yeah.

02:20.750 --> 02:23.083
Look, I'm just saying manage
your expectations, you know.

02:23.083 --> 02:25.083
I-I know the guy.

02:26.458 --> 02:28.959
Well, thanks for the advice.

02:28.959 --> 02:31.708
Warning. Whatever that was.

02:31.708 --> 02:32.834
[knock on door]

02:32.834 --> 02:34.291
Get out here now, guys.

02:34.291 --> 02:36.291
Vanessa's calling
an emergency meeting.

02:39.792 --> 02:41.333
Gather up, Hellcats.

02:43.125 --> 02:45.625
The university is pulling
our funding for regionals.

02:45.625 --> 02:48.333
Wait. What? Why?
We-we just qualified.

02:48.333 --> 02:52.500
The girls volleyball team
also qualified in their league.

02:52.500 --> 02:54.667
The school was paying
to send us and not them.

02:54.667 --> 02:56.291
The ladies didn't think
that was fair

02:56.291 --> 02:57.750
and they're filing a lawsuit
against the school.

02:57.750 --> 02:59.166
[scoffs]

02:59.166 --> 03:01.375
I hate them,
but that is genius.

03:01.375 --> 03:04.667
The NCAA recognizes
volleyball as a sport.

03:04.667 --> 03:06.959
'Cheerleading, not so much.'

03:06.959 --> 03:09.375
The university is looking
to avoid a legal fight

03:09.375 --> 03:12.000
and so they are reallocating
our funding to volleyball.

03:12.000 --> 03:13.583
So we can't move
to the next level?

03:13.583 --> 03:15.917
Well, we qualified,
so we're free to go

03:15.917 --> 03:18.166
providing that we can
figure out how to pay

03:18.166 --> 03:22.375
for our away uniforms,
entrance fees, travel.

03:23.625 --> 03:25.500
If we foot
the bill ourselves

03:25.500 --> 03:29.208
uh, it breaks down
to about ten grand.

03:29.208 --> 03:31.583
- Oh, my gosh.
- What, so that's it?

03:31.583 --> 03:33.834
- We're done?
- Oh, we're never done.

03:33.834 --> 03:35.708
(Vanessa)
'We're just moving on
to plan B.'

03:35.708 --> 03:39.750
There are two ways
to get to nationals.

03:39.750 --> 03:43.166
'We can go step-by-step
from regionals to sectionals'

03:43.166 --> 03:46.041
'all the way to nationals
building our routines.'

03:49.542 --> 03:52.375
Or since we don't have
the money we need

03:52.375 --> 03:56.083
the second option
is to submit a bid video

03:56.083 --> 03:59.041
directly to the national
organization.

03:59.041 --> 04:00.708
The competition's
a lot stiffer.

04:00.708 --> 04:02.375
But if we win a bid

04:02.375 --> 04:04.417
the national organization
pays our full freight.

04:04.417 --> 04:06.542
If it's free, why didn't we just
do that in the first place?

04:06.542 --> 04:08.875
- Well, because of you.
- Alice--

04:08.875 --> 04:11.041
It's the truth.

04:11.041 --> 04:13.458
Vanessa is afraid to put
an inexperienced flyer like you

04:13.458 --> 04:16.666
on video up against
the best stunters in the nation.

04:17.750 --> 04:20.416
Wow. Okay.

04:20.416 --> 04:23.375
Hey, look, we all have
total faith in you, Marti.

04:23.375 --> 04:26.083
And may I remind everyone
that if it wasn't for Marti

04:26.083 --> 04:27.708
we would not
have won at qualifiers.

04:27.708 --> 04:31.083
- Exactly.
- Yes. Marti! Whoo!

04:31.083 --> 04:32.750
(Alice)
'Come on, we all know
we're just marking time'

04:32.750 --> 04:34.375
until my wrist healed
enough for me to come back

04:34.375 --> 04:36.333
and take my rightful spot.

04:36.333 --> 04:39.000
Okay, it sucks
to be sidelined with an injury.

04:39.000 --> 04:41.750
I know, and I'm sorry, but your
wrist needs time to heal.

04:41.750 --> 04:44.750
My wrist is fine.
It doesn't even hurt anymore.

04:44.750 --> 04:47.750
If we're shooting a video,
you need me on that mat.

04:47.750 --> 04:49.083
You guys, tell her.

04:49.083 --> 04:51.208
Hey, um, look.

04:51.208 --> 04:52.583
I know this is the worst
possible timing

04:52.583 --> 04:54.792
but I can't be late
for this seminar again.

04:54.792 --> 04:57.125
Guys, I'm-I'm sorry.

04:57.125 --> 04:58.959
[sighs]

04:58.959 --> 05:01.166
Alice, you are a treat
as always.

05:01.166 --> 05:03.375
Glad the, uh, wrist injury
didn't affect your claws.

05:06.250 --> 05:07.792
She's not even a real Hellcat.

05:07.792 --> 05:10.792
She is just using us
to pay for her law classes.

05:10.792 --> 05:12.959
The sooner I'm back
on the mat, the better.

05:30.500 --> 05:33.250
(Julian)
Oh, Miss Perkins.

05:33.250 --> 05:36.500
In a court of law, what happens
when one party is late?

05:36.500 --> 05:39.333
The, um, late party
is held in contempt.

05:39.333 --> 05:41.625
That's correct.

05:41.625 --> 05:43.917
But that's not
the real punishment.

05:43.917 --> 05:47.125
Does anyone know what
the real punishment is?

05:47.125 --> 05:48.333
Mr. Pepper.

05:48.333 --> 05:49.959
The judge and jury

05:49.959 --> 05:52.834
those who dictate
the outcome of your case

05:52.834 --> 05:54.500
they won't take you seriously.

05:54.500 --> 05:57.500
In the American justice system,
perception is reality--

05:57.500 --> 06:00.708
Please stop speaking,
Mr. Pepper.

06:00.708 --> 06:03.458
Have a seat.

06:03.458 --> 06:06.583
'As I was saying, there are
two types of litigators.'

06:06.583 --> 06:08.500
'Rich ones who rack up
the billable hours'

06:08.500 --> 06:11.959
and those with a soft spot
for the lost causes.

06:11.959 --> 06:14.458
The kind of cases no one else
is willing to touch

06:14.458 --> 06:16.875
and who find themselves teaching
at Lancer to pay their rent.

06:16.875 --> 06:18.542
[chuckles]

06:18.542 --> 06:21.333
'Now, I have taken on
yet another lost cause.'

06:21.333 --> 06:23.834
A man who has been sentenced
to life in prison

06:23.834 --> 06:26.375
for a minor burglary.

06:26.375 --> 06:29.208
And we are gonna get him out.

06:29.208 --> 06:32.333
So I need two pre-law
students to help me

06:32.333 --> 06:35.917
'with research
and interviews and legwork.'

06:35.917 --> 06:38.667
So sign your names
for consideration.

06:40.375 --> 06:42.417
You know, Harvard and Yale Law,
they love when they see

06:42.417 --> 06:44.417
'those kind of side projects
on a transcript.'

06:44.417 --> 06:47.041
Beware, this is not easy.

06:47.041 --> 06:49.208
You will work harder
than you ever have.

06:49.208 --> 06:52.750
And if there's any blood,
sweat or tears left at the end

06:52.750 --> 06:54.875
you're not doin' it right.

06:54.875 --> 06:57.875
It'll be the worst time
of your life

06:57.875 --> 06:59.834
but it'll also be the best.

07:05.083 --> 07:07.125
So if you are not serious...

07:08.417 --> 07:10.208
...do not bother.

07:32.208 --> 07:34.834
Ow, ow, ow.
I'm, I'm coming down.

07:36.625 --> 07:39.458
You shouldn't be
on your wrist like that.

07:39.458 --> 07:41.625
'I think you guys
should call it a day.'

07:41.625 --> 07:43.959
- She's right.
- I can get this.

07:43.959 --> 07:47.500
I need to be ready
for the bid video. Come on.

07:47.500 --> 07:49.625
Is this really
about the bid video?

07:49.625 --> 07:52.166
Or is it about Lewis?

07:52.166 --> 07:53.917
Lewis? No.

07:53.917 --> 07:56.708
You're pushing yourself because
you wanna be his flyer again.

07:56.708 --> 07:58.333
Okay. You're talking crap.

07:58.333 --> 08:01.417
Dr. Derrick is not gonna
clear you with a bum wrist.

08:01.417 --> 08:03.458
My wrist is-is fine.

08:05.291 --> 08:06.959
Ow.

08:06.959 --> 08:10.041
If you can't fool me,
how are you gonna fool a doctor?

08:18.458 --> 08:19.625
[78violet singing "The Good,
The Bad and The Boring]

08:27.166 --> 08:28.583
(Alice)
'Hey, Jake.'

08:30.125 --> 08:35.500
♪ Somehow I can get out ♪♪

08:35.500 --> 08:38.000
Hello, darlin'.

08:38.000 --> 08:39.332
Lewis know you're here?

08:39.332 --> 08:42.500
- Lewis and I broke up.
- Huh.

08:42.500 --> 08:44.792
You know, I never understood
what you saw in him, anyway.

08:44.792 --> 08:46.708
What happened between you guys?

08:46.708 --> 08:48.667
You used to be all
Judd Apatow for each other

08:48.667 --> 08:51.834
and then one day, boom, you
suddenly hate each other's guts.

08:51.834 --> 08:54.125
Yeah, well, he abandoned
his team. He's a traitor.

08:54.125 --> 08:56.166
Nothing much else to say.

08:56.166 --> 08:58.667
Boys and their secrets.

08:58.667 --> 09:01.625
Anyway, I need your help.

09:01.625 --> 09:04.708
- Mm-hmm.
- I have to pass medical.

09:07.166 --> 09:08.208
How long ago did you injure it?

09:08.208 --> 09:09.750
A few weeks.

09:09.750 --> 09:12.875
I'm about a month out
from unassisted recovery.

09:12.875 --> 09:14.542
I don't have that kind of time.

09:14.542 --> 09:18.875
Okay. Well, I can get you
oxy and vikes for the pain

09:18.875 --> 09:20.917
but you're gonna
want HGH as well.

09:20.917 --> 09:22.333
It'll cut the healing time
in half and you can

09:22.333 --> 09:24.041
practice in the meantime.

09:24.041 --> 09:27.875
Oh. What's it gonna cost me?

09:29.250 --> 09:31.208
Oh, Alice.

09:31.208 --> 09:32.208
I don't know,
let's meet up later tonight

09:32.208 --> 09:33.667
and figure something out.

09:33.667 --> 09:36.583
- Sounds like a plan.
- Yeah?

09:36.583 --> 09:39.125
I'll text you and let you know
where I'll be.

09:43.667 --> 09:45.542
The Third Circuit ruled
the three-strikes law

09:45.542 --> 09:47.250
unconstitutional
because it resulted

09:47.250 --> 09:49.250
in cruel and unusual punishment.

09:49.250 --> 09:50.750
Butters had
already served six years--

09:50.750 --> 09:52.750
Why not just overturn the law?

09:52.750 --> 09:54.917
Three-strike laws
are political plutonium.

09:54.917 --> 09:57.875
Nobody wants to be accused
of, of going easy on a criminal

09:57.875 --> 09:59.875
so nobody attacks
the larger issue.

09:59.875 --> 10:03.458
That these laws are
fundamentally unconstitutional.

10:03.458 --> 10:04.875
You're quoting me.

10:04.875 --> 10:07.417
"University of Chicago
Law Review, Volume 64."

10:07.417 --> 10:10.458
Look, you've-you've clearly,
you've done your homework.

10:10.458 --> 10:13.625
And I, I wanna thank you
for your time.

10:13.625 --> 10:16.875
Wait, that's it?
Did I do something wrong?

10:16.875 --> 10:18.542
Your answers are acceptable,
Miss Perkins.

10:18.542 --> 10:20.208
Your grades are good.
You're solid.

10:20.208 --> 10:24.792
But I need serious and committed
students, not cheerleaders.

10:24.792 --> 10:27.291
The reason I'm a cheerleader's
because I need the scholarship.

10:27.291 --> 10:29.417
I don't care why. The point
is you're overextended.

10:29.417 --> 10:31.291
I see you sliding into my class
at the last minute.

10:31.291 --> 10:33.250
You got bags under your eyes.

10:33.250 --> 10:36.625
Placing you on my team
would be an enormous risk.

10:36.625 --> 10:38.917
And this case is too important
for that.

10:38.917 --> 10:40.125
A man's freedom
is on the line.

10:40.125 --> 10:42.333
You know, I can make the time.

10:42.333 --> 10:44.750
If I have to, I'll cut back on
eating, sleeping and showering.

10:44.750 --> 10:48.667
I promise I will work 24/7
and I will impress you.

10:52.125 --> 10:53.875
I will give you one chance.

10:56.917 --> 10:59.083
It's a side assignment, but
you gotta keep it confidential.

10:59.083 --> 11:00.834
Alright? I don't want
your classmates hounding me.

11:00.834 --> 11:02.333
Yeah.

11:02.333 --> 11:04.166
Before our next class,
I want you to research

11:04.166 --> 11:06.917
Kobayashi v. Tennessee

11:06.917 --> 11:10.625
and how it applies
to three-strikes laws.

11:10.625 --> 11:12.834
- Got it?
- I got it.

11:14.333 --> 11:16.875
And do us all a favor.

11:16.875 --> 11:18.542
Keep on showering.

11:26.792 --> 11:29.291
[indistinct chatter]

11:29.291 --> 11:32.667
- Okay? Just stay focused.
- Alright. Thanks, coach.

11:36.834 --> 11:38.583
- Boo!
- Oh!

11:39.834 --> 11:42.667
Are you trying to avoid me?

11:42.667 --> 11:46.125
I forgot my whistle.

11:46.125 --> 11:48.625
So I just went back in
to get it.

11:48.625 --> 11:51.166
Why are you lurking
outside my door, anyway?

11:51.166 --> 11:53.208
I'm enjoying
all the intrigue.

11:53.208 --> 11:55.208
The skulking around

11:55.208 --> 11:58.333
whispered conversations
in hallways.

11:58.333 --> 12:01.875
Come on. Remember how much
fun that used to be?

12:01.875 --> 12:03.583
Is this a game for you?

12:03.583 --> 12:06.583
Asking Derrick and me
to have drinks with you

12:06.583 --> 12:08.875
sending me roses,
bringing the football team

12:08.875 --> 12:10.708
to cheer for us at qualifiers.

12:10.708 --> 12:11.875
You're the one
keeping your boyfriend

12:11.875 --> 12:15.708
in the dark
about our history. Not me.

12:15.708 --> 12:20.208
I was a student having
an affair with a faculty member.

12:20.208 --> 12:22.583
A stupid, immature cliche.

12:22.583 --> 12:25.250
I didn't want Derrick
to think any less of me

12:25.250 --> 12:27.667
so I didn't tell him.

12:27.667 --> 12:30.708
I have another theory.

12:30.708 --> 12:32.291
I think you're not
so sure how you feel

12:32.291 --> 12:34.750
about me coming back to Lancer.

12:34.750 --> 12:37.083
You're keeping
your options open.

12:38.375 --> 12:40.083
You're out of your mind.

12:40.083 --> 12:42.583
You always did play
hard to get.

12:42.583 --> 12:45.000
This feels like old times.

12:45.000 --> 12:46.959
What do they call that?

12:46.959 --> 12:49.333
Deja vu? Hm.

12:49.333 --> 12:52.041
I love the French.
They got a name for everything.

12:53.917 --> 12:57.083
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight, coach.

12:58.917 --> 13:00.500
See you tomorrow.

13:03.708 --> 13:05.875
Um, Marti, you busy?

13:05.875 --> 13:07.917
Yeah, I'm tearing my hair out.

13:07.917 --> 13:09.959
My professor gave me
this case to research.

13:09.959 --> 13:13.000
I've searched LexisNexis,
FindLaw, Law-next West.

13:13.000 --> 13:15.125
I even called
the district courts. Nothing.

13:15.125 --> 13:17.125
It's like it doesn't exist.

13:17.125 --> 13:19.291
Why, what's up?

13:19.291 --> 13:21.166
I need you to call Dan.

13:21.166 --> 13:23.083
Tell him I'm sick
and I can't go out with him.

13:23.083 --> 13:25.208
- What?
- It's not really a lie.

13:25.208 --> 13:26.959
My stomach's been
in knots all day.

13:26.959 --> 13:28.792
I thought you were all excited
about the big secular date.

13:28.792 --> 13:31.583
- What happened?
- Everything you said.

13:31.583 --> 13:33.750
About what a player Dan is?

13:33.750 --> 13:36.583
- Oh. This is because of me?
- You're probably right.

13:36.583 --> 13:37.959
He's never gonna be attracted
to someone like me.

13:37.959 --> 13:40.625
Okay, look. I have a big mouth

13:40.625 --> 13:43.667
and I don't always pay attention
to what comes out of it.

13:43.667 --> 13:46.291
It's healthy for you
to get out into the world.

13:46.291 --> 13:48.125
I can't let you blow this off.

13:48.125 --> 13:51.583
- It's not your decision.
- Well, then let me help you.

13:51.583 --> 13:53.417
- But you have to study.
- You know what?

13:53.417 --> 13:58.000
I've hit a wall here, anyways.
A break will do me good.

13:58.000 --> 14:01.166
Now what can we do to keep you
from freaking out?

14:01.166 --> 14:03.625
[Ricki Lee singing
"Can't Touch It"]

14:05.500 --> 14:07.000
♪ Ooh ♪

14:07.000 --> 14:09.458
♪ No no no no ♪

14:09.458 --> 14:14.250
♪ No no no no ♪

14:14.250 --> 14:16.959
♪ Let me see your hands up
in the air ♪

14:16.959 --> 14:20.000
- Hey. How are you?
- Hi. Good.

14:20.000 --> 14:22.166
♪ Shake it all around
yeah yeah ♪

14:22.166 --> 14:24.000
♪ Hey yo you want
a little of this? ♪

14:24.000 --> 14:26.208
♪ You want a little
wanna little of this? ♪

14:26.208 --> 14:28.959
♪ Hey yo you want
a little of this? ♪

14:28.959 --> 14:31.125
It's about that time.

14:31.125 --> 14:33.291
♪ Hey yo you want
a little of this? ♪

14:33.291 --> 14:36.083
♪ You want a little
wanna little of this? ♪

14:36.083 --> 14:38.208
♪ Once you think
you can't touch it ♪♪

